TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(2,4,1);
$b1 = random(2,7,1);
$c1 = random(2,7,1);
$x1 = random(-5,5,1);
$y1 = $a1*$x1*$x1 + $b1*$x1+$c1;
$m1 = 2*$a1*$x1 + $b1;

BEGIN_TEXT
If \( f(x) = $a1 x^2 + $b1 x + $c1 \), find \( f'( $x1 ) \), using the
definition of derivative. \( f'( $x1 ) \) is the limit as \(x\to\) \{ans_rule()\}
of the expression
$BR
\{ans_rule(40)\}
$BR
The value of this limit is
\{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR
END_TEXT

$ans1 = $x1;
$ans2 = "($a1*x**2 + $b1*x + $c1 - $y1)/(x - $x1)";
$ans = $m1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(fun_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

BEGIN_TEXT
Use this to find the equation of the tangent line to the parabola
 \( y = $a1 x^2 + $b1 x + $c1 \)
at the point \( ( $x1 , $y1 ) \).
The equation of this tangent line can be written in the form
$BR
\( y = \) \{ans_rule(40)\}
END_TEXT

$ans = "$m1*x + $y1 -$m1*$x1";
ANS(fun_cmp($ans));


